-- Russia Fights 334 Forest Fires Covering 81,321 Hectares, RIA Novosti Says
-- Patrick Henry
-- 2010-07-28T07:07:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/russia-fights-334-forest-fires-covering-81-321-hectares-ria-novosti-says.html

          
          
             Russian emergency crews are fighting
334 forest fires covering an area of 81,321 hectares (just over
200,000 acres), RIA Novosti reported, citing an unidentified
Emergency Situations Ministry official.  
 Firefighters extinguished 367 blazes in the last 24 hours,
including 47 fires on peat bogs drained for agriculture in the
Soviet era, the state-run news service reported today, citing
the official.  
 Russian authorities have deployed 8,902 firefighters to
battle the flames across central Russia and 46 aircraft, RIA
reported.  
 Since the start of the fire season, 21,209 fires have
claimed 449,634 hectares of forest, RIA said.  
          
          


  


        